WEBVTT

00:32.165 --> 00:33.232
MAN: Zoya.

00:35.236 --> 00:37.036
-[DOOR OPENS]
-Zoya.

00:54.555 --> 00:55.821
Oh.

01:17.244 --> 01:18.777
[MUFFLED WHIMPERING]

01:22.216 --> 01:25.117
-[JANGLING]
-[WOMAN SOBBING]

01:34.328 --> 01:35.861
[WHIMPERING]

01:56.550 --> 01:58.317
[WOMAN SOBBING]

02:25.146 --> 02:26.912
MAN: Welcome to paradise.

02:42.563 --> 02:43.862
[KEYS JINGLING]

03:33.814 --> 03:36.014
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING
ON EARPHONES]

03:46.260 --> 03:47.926
-[KNOCK ON DOOR]
-MAN: Zoya?

03:53.867 --> 03:55.667
-[KNOCK ON DOOR]
-MAN: Zoya.

04:02.376 --> 04:03.442
[IN HINDI]

04:42.383 --> 04:43.548
[IN HINDI]

05:17.885 --> 05:18.950
MAN: Liam!

05:20.821 --> 05:22.387
Liam!

05:22.389 --> 05:23.622
LIAM: [IN ENGLISH]
Yes, Father?

05:33.367 --> 05:34.433
MAN: Liam!

05:35.002 --> 05:36.501
LIAM: Yes, Father?

05:36.503 --> 05:38.103
MAN: Did you get my stuff?

05:38.906 --> 05:40.405
LIAM: Yes, Father.

05:40.407 --> 05:41.873
MAN: What took you so long?

05:41.875 --> 05:45.577
God. Kids nowadays.

05:45.579 --> 05:47.979
LIAM: I'm sorry, Father.
I got delayed on the way.

05:48.649 --> 05:49.981
[CELL PHONE CHIMING]

06:17.010 --> 06:18.410
MAN: Liam.

06:20.013 --> 06:22.848
When am I getting my...
My real stuff?

06:22.850 --> 06:23.915
Soon.

06:24.585 --> 06:25.851
MAN: Soon?

06:25.853 --> 06:28.086
It's been a long
dry run for me.

06:28.088 --> 06:29.888
You realize that, don't you?

06:29.890 --> 06:31.623
I have been busy.

06:32.159 --> 06:34.926
MAN: [SCOFFS] Busy.

06:34.928 --> 06:38.196
Back home in Ireland,
my father used to say to me,

06:38.198 --> 06:43.135
"Son, unwillingness
easily finds an excuse."

06:44.638 --> 06:46.071
I said soon.

06:46.073 --> 06:47.873
Fingers crossed.

06:49.543 --> 06:54.446
NOEL: That's like a good boy.
[CHUCKLING]

06:54.448 --> 06:55.647
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]

07:41.128 --> 07:43.929
-[DOORKNOB RATTLING]
-[ZOYA WHIMPERING]

07:50.170 --> 07:51.937
[KEYS JANGLING]

08:04.852 --> 08:06.952
[ZOYA WHIMPERING]

08:09.890 --> 08:11.089
[FLY UNZIPPING]

08:11.959 --> 08:13.625
[MUFFLED GRUNTING]

08:16.930 --> 08:18.063
[SOBBING]

08:24.972 --> 08:26.004
[DOOR SHUTS]

08:26.006 --> 08:27.606
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

08:37.551 --> 08:38.683
[MOANING]

08:50.898 --> 08:52.197
Did you sleep well?

08:52.199 --> 08:54.099
[MUFFLED SCREAM]

09:02.576 --> 09:03.742
[KEYS JINGLING]

09:08.348 --> 09:12.317
"The thief comes only to kill,
and steal, and destroy.

09:15.222 --> 09:17.155
"I have come
so you may have life.

09:19.226 --> 09:20.692
"And have it to the full."

09:27.100 --> 09:28.166
[KNIFE SCRAPING]

09:29.369 --> 09:30.602
[MUFFLED SCREAM]

09:36.710 --> 09:40.045
"For I am with you,
and no one's going to
attack and harm you."

09:41.381 --> 09:42.881
[ZOYA COUGHS]

09:42.883 --> 09:44.049
[IN HINDI]

09:46.587 --> 09:47.953
[IN ENGLISH] Let me go!

09:47.955 --> 09:49.654
[SOBBING]

09:49.656 --> 09:51.656
Bastard! Just let me go!

09:51.658 --> 09:54.059
Let me go! Bastard!

09:55.996 --> 09:58.063
[SOBBING] Let me go.

10:01.068 --> 10:03.034
Save your breath, my angel.

10:03.036 --> 10:04.202
It's pointless.

10:05.005 --> 10:06.371
We're far from civilization.

10:06.373 --> 10:07.606
[ZOYA SOBBING]

10:24.658 --> 10:26.424
My angel,

10:26.426 --> 10:28.226
in this dark place
that you're in,

10:30.030 --> 10:31.930
I'm your knight
in shining armor.

10:33.000 --> 10:34.065
[ZOYA SOBBING]

11:03.063 --> 11:04.729
[LIAM EXHALES]

11:16.443 --> 11:17.942
[KEYS JANGLING]

11:33.260 --> 11:34.459
Who are you?

11:36.430 --> 11:38.963
Who's that other man
who tricked me into this?

11:40.267 --> 11:41.399
He's Conan.

11:42.169 --> 11:43.268
My brother.

11:46.073 --> 11:47.238
And you?

11:49.176 --> 11:51.076
[SNICKERS] Who am I?

11:52.479 --> 11:54.479
Isn't every one of us
searching for that answer?

11:55.415 --> 11:56.948
"Who am I?"

12:01.421 --> 12:02.921
What's the time now?

12:05.092 --> 12:06.925
[SNICKERS]

12:06.927 --> 12:09.511
Someone once said,

12:09.512 --> 12:12.096
"To realize
the unimportance of time
is the gate to wisdom."

12:16.069 --> 12:17.435
What's the date today?

12:17.437 --> 12:20.171
[SNICKERS] Today is
a memorable day.

12:21.141 --> 12:23.374
Kevin Rudd
and Malcolm Turnbull

12:23.376 --> 12:25.910
have apologized
to the Stolen Generation

12:25.912 --> 12:30.081
for the abuse,
neglect and suffering
endured all those years.

12:35.388 --> 12:37.021
What do you want?

12:41.428 --> 12:42.961
I just want love.

12:43.563 --> 12:44.796
That's all.

12:47.234 --> 12:48.533
My father can give you money.

12:49.402 --> 12:50.935
Lots of money.

12:50.937 --> 12:53.404
Aren't you afraid?

12:53.406 --> 12:55.306
The cops will come
looking for you.

13:04.384 --> 13:06.284
The cops will come
looking for my brother.

13:08.955 --> 13:10.021
Not me.

13:14.361 --> 13:16.194
I want to know the time.

13:16.196 --> 13:18.096
[SNICKERS]

13:18.098 --> 13:19.364
[SIGHS]

13:20.433 --> 13:22.066
Love is timeless.

13:22.569 --> 13:24.102
It is priceless.

13:25.238 --> 13:27.205
It's very important
in one's life.

13:27.874 --> 13:29.474
More than money.

13:29.476 --> 13:31.342
More than anything
you can imagine.

13:34.114 --> 13:37.015
Do you know why
King Edward VIII abdicated
the British throne?

13:45.192 --> 13:47.492
In order to marry
the woman he loved.

13:51.431 --> 13:54.999
ZOYA: Please tell me
what time it is.

13:55.001 --> 13:59.070
And I'm no different
to King Edward VIII
when it comes to love.

13:59.072 --> 14:01.372
[SOFT INSTRUMENTAL
MUSIC PLAYING]

14:22.996 --> 14:24.229
[GASPING]

14:39.045 --> 14:40.378
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

14:44.484 --> 14:46.050
[TICKING]

14:53.927 --> 14:57.061
[SCREAMING AND SOBBING]

15:09.442 --> 15:10.975
[CLOCK TICKING]

15:21.922 --> 15:23.288
[TICKING INTENSIFIES]

15:27.060 --> 15:28.426
[CLOCK TICKING]

15:31.164 --> 15:32.964
[ZOYA'S FATHER SPEAKING HINDI]

16:25.218 --> 16:26.484
[IN HINDI]

16:36.396 --> 16:37.762
[PENCIL SCRATCHING]

16:37.764 --> 16:40.298
[SOFT INSTRUMENTAL
MUSIC PLAYING]

16:59.119 --> 17:00.785
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

17:03.089 --> 17:04.489
[ZOYA GASPING]

17:36.089 --> 17:37.822
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

17:48.568 --> 17:50.068
[IN ENGLISH]
Can I have a cigarette?

17:53.540 --> 17:55.073
LIAM: "Please."

17:56.209 --> 17:57.375
ZOYA: Please.

17:59.546 --> 18:02.146
Cigarette smoking
is injurious to health.

18:06.886 --> 18:08.119
[ZOYA EXHALES]

18:08.755 --> 18:10.388
I'm dying for a smoke.

18:12.826 --> 18:14.192
Please?

18:16.763 --> 18:18.262
What you need is liquid.

18:19.232 --> 18:20.398
Not gas.

18:32.445 --> 18:35.613
Did you know,
about 52 Australians
die each day from smoking?

18:41.154 --> 18:42.420
I wish to die.

19:03.943 --> 19:05.376
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

19:22.328 --> 19:23.828
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

19:47.320 --> 19:48.486
[GRUNTS SOFTLY]

20:06.239 --> 20:07.305
[GRUNTS SOFTLY]

20:12.812 --> 20:14.845
-[ZOYA GASPING]
-Hello, sweetheart.

20:14.847 --> 20:15.947
Looking for me?

20:15.949 --> 20:17.448
[ZOYA SCREAMING]

20:21.788 --> 20:22.987
[SNIFFING]

20:24.324 --> 20:26.524
Next time you scream,

20:26.526 --> 20:28.559
I'm gonna squeeze
the life out of you.

20:29.762 --> 20:31.495
Do I make myself clear?

20:32.465 --> 20:33.531
Mmm.

20:34.867 --> 20:36.934
-[SOBBING]
-That's a good girl.

20:38.271 --> 20:40.271
My angel,

20:40.273 --> 20:43.841
I know life's not
exactly exciting with Liam.

20:43.843 --> 20:46.477
But with me... [CHUCKLES]

20:46.479 --> 20:48.546
Well, that's a different story.

20:48.548 --> 20:49.680
NOEL: Liam!

20:50.416 --> 20:52.617
[ZOYA GASPING]

20:52.619 --> 20:55.586
Have you heard the story about
the frog in the boiling water?

20:56.489 --> 20:59.006
No?

20:59.007 --> 21:01.524
Well, if you drop a frog
into boiling water,

21:01.527 --> 21:03.327
it will jump out immediately.

21:03.329 --> 21:04.428
NOEL: Liam!

21:06.566 --> 21:09.900
But if you place a frog
into normal water,

21:09.902 --> 21:12.937
slowly turn up
the heat to boiling,

21:12.939 --> 21:15.806
the frog won't feel
the heat change.

21:15.808 --> 21:17.875
It'll continue to play.

21:17.877 --> 21:20.878
But it will eventually die.

21:21.814 --> 21:22.880
NOEL: Liam!

21:23.616 --> 21:25.483
[EXHALES ANGRILY]

21:25.485 --> 21:26.917
[ZOYA GASPING]

21:29.289 --> 21:30.388
Nice dress.

21:31.491 --> 21:34.458
But nice girls
look lovely without them.

21:34.460 --> 21:35.893
NOEL: Come here at once.

21:35.895 --> 21:38.396
CONAN: Old man never stops.
Where does he get the energy?

21:38.398 --> 21:40.498
-Now where is Liam?
-[DOOR SHUTS]

21:40.500 --> 21:41.932
[ZOYA GASPING]

22:21.474 --> 22:22.707
[GASPS]

22:30.550 --> 22:32.083
Please save me.

22:35.455 --> 22:37.655
Please let me
go back to my family.

22:41.160 --> 22:43.127
Or you can stay with me here.

22:44.931 --> 22:46.997
And your brother
will not come back then.

22:53.573 --> 22:55.139
He's as good as dead to me.

23:00.813 --> 23:02.913
I wish I could stay
with you, my angel.

23:04.884 --> 23:06.684
I've got to work on weekdays.

23:09.555 --> 23:11.722
Then you can
help me escape.

23:16.162 --> 23:18.095
Everybody wants to escape
from someone.

23:22.168 --> 23:23.434
Me, too.

23:27.607 --> 23:29.073
How I miss my mother.

23:31.511 --> 23:32.676
[LIAM INHALES]

23:35.047 --> 23:36.580
I'm afraid of Conan.

23:38.851 --> 23:40.050
And my father.

23:43.956 --> 23:45.923
Sometimes I wish
they were dead.

23:54.567 --> 23:56.133
I wish I could
give you a hug.

24:02.542 --> 24:03.641
Please.

24:05.645 --> 24:06.877
Please.

24:07.647 --> 24:08.913
Please.

24:10.616 --> 24:11.949
I know you can.

24:15.888 --> 24:17.521
You're a nice man.

24:19.058 --> 24:20.458
You're a kind man.

24:22.662 --> 24:24.662
I will do anything you say.

24:26.833 --> 24:28.499
I will do anything.

24:29.669 --> 24:30.901
Please.

24:34.974 --> 24:36.874
[SOBBING] Please.

24:38.511 --> 24:40.744
Please. Please.

24:57.864 --> 24:59.263
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

25:10.543 --> 25:12.643
Where were you
all these days?

25:17.016 --> 25:18.282
LIAM: I tried.

25:20.987 --> 25:22.152
I contacted your father.

25:25.825 --> 25:27.091
I knew you would.

25:29.161 --> 25:31.228
I tried to explain
the danger you're in.

25:32.665 --> 25:33.998
I tried.

25:39.605 --> 25:41.305
At first, he wouldn't listen.

25:41.307 --> 25:42.673
But I persisted.

25:44.877 --> 25:47.645
But he's blindly refused to
have anything to do with you.

25:49.115 --> 25:51.248
In fact...

25:51.250 --> 25:53.284
he's told everyone
you've gone away to India.

25:56.956 --> 25:58.556
He does not want you back.

26:00.092 --> 26:02.059
He says you've brought shame
on the family.

26:07.233 --> 26:08.699
They have disowned you.

26:10.670 --> 26:12.169
So, now you have no home.

26:13.673 --> 26:14.772
No family.

26:17.910 --> 26:19.209
I don't believe you.

26:39.832 --> 26:41.332
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

26:49.041 --> 26:50.240
[DOOR SHUTS]

26:52.278 --> 26:56.046
LIAM: <i> He says you've brought</i>
<i>shame on the family.</i> [ECHOING]

26:56.048 --> 26:57.915
<i> They have disowned you.</i>

26:59.685 --> 27:01.218
<i> So, now you have no home.</i>

27:03.155 --> 27:04.388
<i> No family.</i>

27:14.100 --> 27:15.265
Papa?

27:16.135 --> 27:17.401
I knew you'd come.

27:18.137 --> 27:19.436
I love you, Papa.

27:19.438 --> 27:22.039
MAN: I love you, too,
<i> meri bacchi.</i>

27:22.041 --> 27:23.374
Please help me.

27:24.410 --> 27:25.976
[GASPING]

27:31.083 --> 27:32.349
[GASPING]

27:45.331 --> 27:46.997
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

27:51.337 --> 27:53.370
-[ZOYA GASPS]
-CONAN: Out of my way, Pa.

27:53.372 --> 27:55.873
LIAM: Why are you
going in there?

27:55.875 --> 27:58.108
CONAN: To play Monopoly.

27:58.110 --> 28:01.345
LIAM: Don't upset Father.
Conan, you know
you shouldn't go in there.

28:01.347 --> 28:02.479
CONAN: Oh, who will stop me?

28:02.481 --> 28:06.383
You? Or the old man?
[LAUGHS]

28:06.385 --> 28:09.453
-Liam?
-I'll deal with you later.

28:10.489 --> 28:12.923
I'll deal with you now.

28:14.060 --> 28:16.493
Can you not see
the lady's waiting for me?

28:16.495 --> 28:19.997
Step aside, bro.
Or else I will step over you.

28:19.999 --> 28:21.331
NOEL: Wait, what's going on?

28:21.333 --> 28:23.901
LIAM: Conan,
I will protect her.

28:23.903 --> 28:27.104
Conan, I'm warning you.
Stay away from her
or I will... [GRUNTS]

28:28.240 --> 28:29.306
[GRUNTS]

28:30.910 --> 28:32.342
Don't you worry, sweetheart.

28:32.945 --> 28:34.111
I'll be back.

28:34.480 --> 28:36.180
Very soon.

28:36.182 --> 28:37.948
NOEL: Liam! Liam!

28:37.950 --> 28:39.483
[DOOR SHUTS]

28:39.485 --> 28:41.218
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

29:00.072 --> 29:01.772
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

29:32.138 --> 29:33.337
[SNIFFS]

29:36.242 --> 29:37.775
-[THUDS]
-[WINCES]

29:40.045 --> 29:41.178
[GRUNTS]

29:42.114 --> 29:43.180
[GROANS]

29:50.156 --> 29:51.355
[GRUNTS]

30:05.971 --> 30:07.204
[DOOR OPENS]

30:14.513 --> 30:15.612
[GASPS]

30:41.040 --> 30:42.506
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

31:07.967 --> 31:09.466
My angel, I'm so sorry.

31:10.903 --> 31:13.904
I can't bear
to see you suffer.

31:13.906 --> 31:16.540
I'll gladly risk my life
and take you back
to your family. Only if...

31:28.354 --> 31:29.553
Conan's very evil.

31:33.292 --> 31:35.325
You don't know how
I've survived all these years.

31:36.428 --> 31:37.594
Unloved...

31:39.064 --> 31:40.264
and in fear.

32:55.107 --> 32:57.174
[DOOR OPENS AND SHUTS]

33:10.522 --> 33:12.489
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING
AND RINGING]

33:22.301 --> 33:24.001
Hello, Arif speaking.

33:24.003 --> 33:25.535
[PANTING]

33:26.271 --> 33:28.305
I'm really sorry, Papa.

33:28.307 --> 33:29.506
I'm really sorry.

33:35.814 --> 33:39.016
[SOBBING]
Please, Papa, help me!

33:39.018 --> 33:40.150
Please!

33:41.720 --> 33:44.388
[SOBBING] Papa?

33:45.557 --> 33:46.623
[GASPS]

33:53.432 --> 33:55.132
[SOBBING]

33:59.471 --> 34:01.271
[ARIF SPEAKING HINDI]

34:29.868 --> 34:35.172
[IN ENGLISH] "How could I deny
my own faith and my beliefs?

34:35.174 --> 34:38.308
"On the other hand, how could
I deny my own daughter?"

34:40.779 --> 34:42.079
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

34:50.089 --> 34:51.655
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

35:30.562 --> 35:33.396
NOEL: Liam,
please get my mail.

35:46.512 --> 35:48.478
ZOYA: It is so dark in here.

35:48.480 --> 35:50.380
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

36:37.462 --> 36:39.196
My angel,

36:39.198 --> 36:42.299
it's not me who's
making you a recluse.

36:42.301 --> 36:45.869
Just how many years must pass
until a lie becomes the truth?

36:51.810 --> 36:54.778
"How many tears of sorrow
must be shed

36:54.780 --> 36:57.447
"Until they turn
to tears of joy?

36:57.449 --> 37:00.250
"Don't let the past
destroy our chance

37:00.252 --> 37:03.620
"For the future, my angel
don't be coy

37:03.622 --> 37:06.990
"Angel, let go
Don't wait for any intervention

37:07.759 --> 37:10.260
"It is me and only me

37:10.262 --> 37:12.662
BOTH: "Who can provide you
with redemption"

37:23.875 --> 37:25.442
[ZOYA CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

37:45.797 --> 37:46.963
[ZOYA CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

38:03.282 --> 38:04.514
[ZOYA CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

38:17.696 --> 38:18.762
[GASPS]

38:20.732 --> 38:22.332
I'm back, sweetheart.

38:22.334 --> 38:23.466
[DOORBELL RINGS]

38:26.371 --> 38:27.671
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

38:31.376 --> 38:33.310
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

38:38.083 --> 38:39.783
LIAM: Good morning.
OFFICER: Morning.

38:39.785 --> 38:41.451
I'm Detective Singh.

38:44.122 --> 38:46.056
Detective Kollie.

38:46.058 --> 38:48.425
From the Darlington
Police Station.

38:48.427 --> 38:50.427
Making inquiries
of a missing girl.

38:50.696 --> 38:52.062
You are?

38:52.064 --> 38:53.496
Liam. [CLEARS THROAT]

38:53.498 --> 38:55.665
Liam McFarlane.

38:55.667 --> 38:57.634
We would like
to ask you some questions.

38:57.636 --> 38:58.835
Can we come in, please?

39:02.507 --> 39:03.573
LIAM: Yeah, sure.

39:18.056 --> 39:19.489
SINGH: How are you today?

39:20.392 --> 39:21.458
NOEL: Liam.

39:21.460 --> 39:23.393
Do we have visitors?

39:23.395 --> 39:25.695
LIAM: Yes, Father.

39:25.697 --> 39:29.065
We are detectives from
the Darlington Police Station,

39:29.067 --> 39:31.835
making inquiries
about a missing girl.

39:31.837 --> 39:34.170
NOEL: Are you in trouble, Liam?

39:34.172 --> 39:36.439
LIAM: It's my father.
KOLLIE: His name?

39:36.441 --> 39:38.441
Uh, Noel McFarlane.

39:38.443 --> 39:40.176
He used to work
for a bank in the city.

39:41.179 --> 39:42.645
SINGH: Where does he work now?

39:42.647 --> 39:45.448
Uh, he doesn't anymore. Um...

39:45.450 --> 39:48.451
He... He left the bank probably
after my mother passed away.

39:48.453 --> 39:51.588
Things went downhill for him
after that and, well...

39:51.590 --> 39:54.057
He's not been
in the best of state since.

39:54.059 --> 39:56.159
He depends on me
for everything.

39:56.161 --> 39:59.429
He used to have friends,
but they're no more.

39:59.431 --> 40:01.798
SINGH: Is anyone else
staying here?

40:01.800 --> 40:03.666
Oh, no,
it's just the two of us.

40:03.668 --> 40:04.801
Father and son.

40:08.840 --> 40:10.407
NOEL: Officer, I...

40:10.409 --> 40:12.876
I swear on
my dead wife's grave.

40:12.878 --> 40:14.811
God rest her soul.

40:14.813 --> 40:16.679
I've done no wrong.

40:16.681 --> 40:18.615
LIAM: No one is doubting you.

40:18.617 --> 40:20.884
Can you please leave
my dead mother out of this?

40:23.688 --> 40:26.589
Although he never leaves
his room, he wants to know
everything that's going on.

40:29.594 --> 40:31.761
SINGH: Let me tell you
about the missing girl.

40:31.763 --> 40:34.197
She has been missing
for more than six months.

40:34.900 --> 40:36.166
NOEL: Who's missing?

40:36.168 --> 40:38.868
SINGH: She's 19 years of age.

40:38.870 --> 40:43.173
158 centimeters in height,
and small build.

40:43.175 --> 40:47.243
Last seen,
she was wearing a dark top
and ripped jeans.

40:49.080 --> 40:50.547
She's from Bathurst.

40:51.750 --> 40:54.818
NOEL: Back home,
no one went missing.

40:54.820 --> 40:57.120
Everyone kept a lookout
for one another.

40:58.490 --> 40:59.856
But we're far from Bathurst.

41:04.062 --> 41:07.130
She's of Asian background,
but she speaks English well.

41:08.567 --> 41:09.732
Have you see her?

41:17.909 --> 41:19.142
Sorry.

41:21.580 --> 41:22.745
Take a look.

41:24.749 --> 41:26.549
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

41:36.661 --> 41:38.194
SINGH: How long
have you lived here?

41:39.231 --> 41:40.730
I... I was born here.

41:40.732 --> 41:43.233
And my father,
he migrated from Ireland

41:43.235 --> 41:45.134
when he was young,
after the war.

41:45.136 --> 41:47.187
SINGH: And your mother?

41:47.188 --> 41:49.239
[SNICKERS] My moth...
Mother was from Broken Hill.

41:49.241 --> 41:51.207
She was a beautiful woman.

41:51.209 --> 41:52.275
Angelic.

41:54.145 --> 41:56.579
I also had a brother,
but, um, he died young.

41:57.816 --> 41:59.782
NOEL: Why are
you talking softly?

42:00.719 --> 42:02.185
Is anything wrong?

42:04.122 --> 42:07.290
He thinks everyone blames him
for anything that goes wrong
around hm.

42:07.292 --> 42:09.592
He had a nasty temper,

42:09.594 --> 42:13.897
and he often beat his wife,
my... My mother.

42:13.899 --> 42:17.767
So, when she died
in an accident, he thought
everyone blamed him.

42:19.704 --> 42:21.704
[NOEL CHUCKLING]

42:21.706 --> 42:23.106
NOEL: D... Do you know
the difference

42:23.108 --> 42:26.309
between an Irish marriage
and an Irish funeral?

42:27.345 --> 42:30.580
There's one less drunk.
[LAUGHING]

42:38.924 --> 42:41.324
LIAM: Do you have any suspects?

42:41.326 --> 42:43.726
She was last seen
with a Caucasian man

42:43.728 --> 42:46.796
sporting long hair
and wearing a black cap.

42:46.798 --> 42:49.232
He was more or less affable.

42:54.272 --> 42:55.638
My angel...

42:56.141 --> 42:57.206
She...

42:59.678 --> 43:01.377
She... [CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]

43:01.379 --> 43:02.879
I'm his girlfriend.

43:02.881 --> 43:06.282
You mentioned
only two of you live here.

43:06.284 --> 43:07.784
[ZOYA LAUGHING]

43:07.786 --> 43:09.652
He's still not used
to me being here.

43:09.654 --> 43:10.920
What do you mean?

43:11.823 --> 43:13.323
I've not been here for long.

43:20.632 --> 43:24.834
As we say, "See something,
say something,"

43:24.836 --> 43:26.903
if you see or hear
anything suspicious.

43:53.131 --> 43:56.633
All right.
I'll leave you guys to it.
See you later.

44:01.806 --> 44:02.939
Conan is here.

44:16.154 --> 44:18.821
NOEL: [CHUCKLING] Hey, Liam.

44:18.823 --> 44:23.359
I'll tell you the four reasons
why Jesus was Irish.

44:23.361 --> 44:27.430
First, he lived at home
until he was 30.
[LAUGHING]

44:29.901 --> 44:33.670
The second one, he thought
his mother was a virgin.

44:33.672 --> 44:34.937
[CONTINUES LAUGHING]

44:37.208 --> 44:42.345
Third, just before he died,
he went out drinking
with his buddies.

44:43.381 --> 44:44.981
As we do.

44:46.351 --> 44:50.753
And the fourth one, his mother
thought he was God!

44:50.755 --> 44:51.988
[CONTINUES LAUGHING]

45:12.143 --> 45:13.710
Hey, Liam.

45:13.712 --> 45:15.912
Are you off the hook
with the cops?

45:15.914 --> 45:16.979
I don't know.

45:18.116 --> 45:20.183
NOEL: You better
don't involve me.

45:21.519 --> 45:25.121
Hey, do you know they're
making <i> Wolf Creek 2?</i>

45:25.123 --> 45:27.857
Maybe the first
wasn't creepy enough.
[LAUGHS]

45:31.362 --> 45:36.332
Apparently it's based on
the notorious outback
serial killer, Ivan Milat.

45:37.168 --> 45:38.401
What is he saying?

45:40.805 --> 45:45.174
NOEL: As for you,
it's your duty to care for me.

45:45.176 --> 45:47.910
You owe it to me
as a son to a father.

45:49.214 --> 45:50.346
What about me?

45:51.382 --> 45:53.750
You have a duty
to care for me, too.

45:55.153 --> 45:57.353
NOEL: Oh, jeez, you seem to
have forgotten me.

45:59.357 --> 46:00.523
I am.

46:02.393 --> 46:04.160
You've been ignoring me...

46:04.162 --> 46:06.229
Oh, keep quiet, please!

46:06.231 --> 46:07.296
How?

46:08.566 --> 46:09.799
How?

46:12.003 --> 46:13.469
I spoke to Father.

46:15.206 --> 46:17.507
It took me a long time
to convince him

46:17.508 --> 46:19.809
that Conan's presence
in this house isn't good
for any one of us.

46:19.811 --> 46:20.877
He's too violent.

46:20.879 --> 46:22.211
[ZOYA GASPS SOFTLY]

46:22.213 --> 46:24.447
He must have brushed you aside,
you poor thing.

46:25.283 --> 46:27.550
On the contrary.

46:27.552 --> 46:29.786
He's told Conan
to leave this house forever.

46:31.189 --> 46:32.421
You're joking.

46:33.124 --> 46:35.224
We can now live happily.

46:36.127 --> 46:37.593
Happily ever after?

46:37.595 --> 46:40.463
Like they show in the movies?
Oh, my God!

46:44.602 --> 46:46.602
NOEL: Nothing is
the same anymore.

46:47.172 --> 46:49.205
Sick, tired.

47:04.589 --> 47:06.522
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

47:24.142 --> 47:26.909
-[KNOCKING ON DOOR]
-What the hell?

47:26.911 --> 47:28.578
Sorry, Mr. McFarlane.

47:29.547 --> 47:31.914
I just came to thank you.

47:31.916 --> 47:33.482
What... What for?

47:35.486 --> 47:36.986
Regarding Conan?

47:37.922 --> 47:39.121
[NOEL PANTING]

47:39.123 --> 47:41.657
What? Are you
out of your mind?

47:42.493 --> 47:44.160
No.

47:44.162 --> 47:46.128
You told Conan to...

47:46.130 --> 47:49.465
Conan has been dead 22 years.

47:49.467 --> 47:51.467
Why dig up the dead and buried?

47:51.469 --> 47:54.237
And why rub salt
on my wounds?

47:54.873 --> 47:55.905
[SNIFFLING]

47:55.907 --> 47:59.342
How many times I miss...

47:59.344 --> 48:02.945
[SOBBING]
How I miss my boy even now!

48:04.249 --> 48:07.550
How many times have I
mentioned his name

48:07.552 --> 48:11.921
in these 22 years
and wept! [SOBBING]

48:11.923 --> 48:15.558
Conan! Conan!

48:15.560 --> 48:18.561
-Liam said...
-Liam?

48:18.563 --> 48:23.132
He is the root of all evil,
even Conan's death.

48:23.134 --> 48:25.434
Oh, God,
how he disliked Conan!

48:25.436 --> 48:27.470
And how I hated Liam!

48:27.472 --> 48:32.608
Conan, the son I so much
loved and wanted, but lost.

48:34.212 --> 48:36.212
[NOEL SOBBING LOUDLY]

49:01.339 --> 49:02.638
[ZOYA SNIFFLING]

49:33.738 --> 49:35.237
[ZOYA SOBBING]

49:38.609 --> 49:40.543
[RATTLING]

49:54.525 --> 49:56.559
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

50:07.572 --> 50:09.405
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

50:40.438 --> 50:41.670
Welcome home.

50:51.382 --> 50:52.715
Don't you like the new look?

50:53.251 --> 50:54.617
Mmm. Yeah.

50:56.387 --> 50:58.354
It's nice to change things
now and then.

50:59.590 --> 51:02.158
-Change can be unsettling.
-Not necessarily.

51:02.160 --> 51:04.393
Well, if change is
just for the sake of change.

51:05.129 --> 51:06.295
But...

51:06.297 --> 51:08.697
Change is the law of life.

51:11.369 --> 51:12.435
[SIGHS]

51:13.171 --> 51:14.236
This is my home, too.

51:16.641 --> 51:18.240
But...

51:18.242 --> 51:19.642
If you don't like the change,
I will not...

51:19.644 --> 51:21.477
Oh, my angel,
what have you done?

51:42.300 --> 51:43.532
[DOORBELL RINGING]

51:53.678 --> 51:55.511
SINGH: How are you?

51:55.513 --> 51:57.546
I was passing through,
and thought

51:57.548 --> 51:59.582
I didn't talk to
your girlfriend last time.

51:59.584 --> 52:00.716
Is she around?

52:02.453 --> 52:03.819
NOEL: Liam, is that
the cops again?

52:04.689 --> 52:06.222
Yes, Father.

52:08.693 --> 52:11.494
SINGH: Is she there?
Can I come in, please?

52:11.496 --> 52:12.828
Uh, she just left.

52:16.734 --> 52:17.867
ZOYA: Who is it?

52:18.669 --> 52:20.469
Senior Detective Singh.

52:22.573 --> 52:24.740
I was told you had left.

52:24.742 --> 52:27.276
How can I leave?
I have lots to do here.

52:28.412 --> 52:29.478
Where are you from?

52:32.617 --> 52:35.184
Detective Montalbano.

52:35.186 --> 52:36.752
SINGH: Smarter than
the fictional character.

52:38.489 --> 52:39.588
Originally from Lucknow.

52:40.391 --> 52:42.224
-India!
-Yes.

52:42.226 --> 52:44.360
<i> -Namaste.</i>
<i> -Namaste.</i>

52:44.362 --> 52:45.427
[IN HINDI]

52:48.666 --> 52:49.732
Zoya.

52:50.668 --> 52:51.834
[IN HINDI]

52:57.341 --> 52:59.241
[IN HINDI]

52:59.243 --> 53:02.845
[IN ENGLISH] I came here
and I showed you a photo
of a missing girl.

53:02.847 --> 53:04.480
Yes, I remember.

53:04.482 --> 53:06.849
She's still missing.

53:06.851 --> 53:10.219
You took up the photo
and looked at it intensely.

53:10.988 --> 53:12.755
You seemed to recognize her.

53:14.692 --> 53:16.525
I thought she looked familiar.

53:21.666 --> 53:23.265
SINGH: Have you seen her?

53:25.503 --> 53:26.569
No.

53:28.372 --> 53:31.574
It could be her dress
that seemed familiar.

53:31.576 --> 53:33.842
Or maybe I'm imagining things.

53:35.313 --> 53:36.745
What about the dress?

53:42.320 --> 53:43.519
I don't know.

53:45.489 --> 53:48.557
We have information
that she was seen
in this neighborhood.

53:49.260 --> 53:50.392
Did you see her?

54:00.738 --> 54:02.404
Did you see her?

54:14.619 --> 54:16.418
This case is important to me.

54:16.420 --> 54:18.687
I knew Kathy's parents.

54:20.258 --> 54:21.824
[IN HINDI]

54:25.830 --> 54:28.664
[IN ENGLISH] This is my card.
My details have changed.

54:30.468 --> 54:31.533
Congratulations.

54:32.436 --> 54:33.602
Thanks.

54:33.604 --> 54:36.438
Give me a call
if you remember anything.

54:36.440 --> 54:38.707
Or if there is anything else
you want to tell me.

54:40.478 --> 54:41.844
I better let you go now.

54:44.548 --> 54:46.415
We will get the guy.

54:50.688 --> 54:52.388
Thanks again.

54:52.390 --> 54:53.756
[BIRDS SCREECHING]

54:59.764 --> 55:01.363
What?

55:01.365 --> 55:02.831
Cops and lawyers
are a bad omen.

55:04.635 --> 55:05.901
Don't get upset.

55:20.718 --> 55:23.118
Of late, I cannot
get the cops out of my mind.

55:25.089 --> 55:26.622
Why did he come back?

55:27.391 --> 55:28.824
Any idea?

55:28.826 --> 55:31.727
Like he said,
he wanted to talk to you.

55:33.097 --> 55:34.863
He thought that
I knew the missing girl.

55:38.369 --> 55:39.635
I'm getting sick of this.

55:39.637 --> 55:42.538
First, that Indian cop,
and now, you.

55:42.540 --> 55:44.340
He's a Senior Detective.

55:45.343 --> 55:47.109
He seemed very intelligent.

55:47.812 --> 55:49.678
And a handsome man, too.

55:51.148 --> 55:52.681
You think so, do you?

55:53.617 --> 55:54.950
Are you jealous?

55:55.720 --> 55:56.785
No.

55:58.356 --> 56:00.422
You were uncomfortable
when he was around.

56:02.159 --> 56:03.592
What were you thinking?

56:03.594 --> 56:07.763
NOEL: Liam!
Come here at once.

56:08.165 --> 56:09.631
What now?

56:10.868 --> 56:12.134
Why?

56:12.136 --> 56:14.536
Because you've become
a bad son.

56:14.538 --> 56:15.938
I'm busy now.

56:17.641 --> 56:19.608
You're always busy nowadays.

56:19.610 --> 56:20.676
Later.

56:21.579 --> 56:23.512
[BURPS] Later.

56:24.115 --> 56:25.714
I'll be dead by then.

56:28.452 --> 56:29.818
[SIGHS]

56:29.820 --> 56:32.121
I swear I'm gonna
kill him one of these days.

56:32.123 --> 56:33.489
Maybe you should.

56:34.892 --> 56:36.959
I need a drink.
Do you want one?

56:43.734 --> 56:46.468
NOEL: I know
you want me dead.

56:46.470 --> 56:48.670
You have no time for me,

56:48.672 --> 56:52.674
but you have
all the time in the world
for that whore!

56:52.676 --> 56:54.410
[PAWN CLATTERING]

56:58.582 --> 56:59.748
[DOOR OPENS]

57:02.219 --> 57:03.719
[ZOYA BREATHING SHAKILY]

58:04.882 --> 58:06.915
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

58:45.189 --> 58:46.688
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

58:57.768 --> 58:59.234
What are you doing here?

59:02.139 --> 59:03.539
[ZOYA SOBBING]

59:10.314 --> 59:11.947
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

59:50.854 --> 59:52.688
ZOYA: You don't
love me anymore.

59:54.325 --> 59:55.891
I do!

59:55.893 --> 59:58.160
On my dear mother,
I love you
more than anything.

01:00:03.834 --> 01:00:05.767
I often daydream
about our family.

01:00:06.804 --> 01:00:08.670
Can I ask you something?

01:00:08.672 --> 01:00:09.871
Anything you want.

01:00:13.143 --> 01:00:14.676
I just need your love.

01:00:15.412 --> 01:00:17.212
Thank you for everything.

01:00:17.214 --> 01:00:22.184
My angel, my love,
you don't need to thank me.

01:00:22.186 --> 01:00:25.220
Everything here is yours.

01:00:25.222 --> 01:00:28.857
I don't need everything.
I just need you.

01:00:30.160 --> 01:00:31.927
You can do
whatever you want.

01:00:34.798 --> 01:00:36.298
And go wherever?

01:00:37.835 --> 01:00:39.868
Of course, my angel.

01:00:39.870 --> 01:00:41.269
You're not a prisoner here.

01:00:41.939 --> 01:00:43.105
[SIGHS]

01:00:43.107 --> 01:00:46.141
I feel like one, locked.

01:01:06.864 --> 01:01:08.196
[CLATTERING]

01:01:38.696 --> 01:01:40.429
[WATER RUNNING]

01:01:47.104 --> 01:01:49.771
NOEL: I looked after you
when you were young.

01:01:49.773 --> 01:01:51.306
Now, it's your turn.

01:01:52.943 --> 01:01:55.110
Why aren't you
going to work?

01:01:55.112 --> 01:01:58.814
The last few weeks,
all you've done is
play with your toy.

01:01:58.816 --> 01:02:01.817
Poverty waits
at the gates of idleness.

01:02:01.819 --> 01:02:04.119
I lost my job.

01:02:04.121 --> 01:02:05.854
And I'm looking
for another one.

01:02:06.156 --> 01:02:08.223
Why?

01:02:08.224 --> 01:02:10.291
You wouldn't understand.
You don't want to understand.

01:02:10.294 --> 01:02:13.929
Companies are trying
to do more with less.

01:02:13.931 --> 01:02:16.765
NOEL: It's no different
now from then.

01:02:16.767 --> 01:02:19.534
To make matters worse,
these fucking migrants
are everywhere,

01:02:19.536 --> 01:02:20.736
taking everything.

01:02:20.738 --> 01:02:22.904
Mind your language,
young man.

01:02:26.276 --> 01:02:29.845
At this rate,
it may be a long while.
[CHUCKLING]

01:02:29.847 --> 01:02:32.447
-What are you doing now?
-I'm busy.

01:02:32.449 --> 01:02:34.216
Busy with your doll?

01:02:36.286 --> 01:02:38.386
"Do not rejoice
when your enemy falls,

01:02:38.388 --> 01:02:41.456
"and let not your heart
be glad when he stumbles."

01:02:46.230 --> 01:02:48.263
He's never made it
easy for me.

01:02:48.265 --> 01:02:50.966
-He's always treated me like...
-A child?

01:02:50.968 --> 01:02:53.401
Worse. Like shit.

01:02:58.208 --> 01:02:59.808
I don't know what to do.

01:03:02.846 --> 01:03:04.346
What do you want
to have for lunch?

01:03:19.830 --> 01:03:20.896
We need to talk.

01:03:24.268 --> 01:03:26.501
I'm talking to you, Liam.

01:03:26.503 --> 01:03:29.471
Half the morning is gone,
and you're still in bed.

01:03:29.473 --> 01:03:31.339
Remember what your father said?

01:03:31.341 --> 01:03:33.441
Lose an hour in the morning
and you'll be looking for it
all day.

01:03:36.413 --> 01:03:39.281
What's the point
in brooding all day?

01:03:39.283 --> 01:03:41.416
In the last few weeks,
you've hardly stirred.

01:03:43.320 --> 01:03:45.387
[ZOYA SIGHS]

01:03:45.389 --> 01:03:48.190
Who will give you a job
if you don't try?

01:03:48.192 --> 01:03:50.325
No one has achieved anything
without trying.

01:03:50.327 --> 01:03:52.394
-Oh, don't start this again.
-I don't want to.

01:03:52.396 --> 01:03:54.563
But how long can you
provide for us
on government handouts?

01:03:54.565 --> 01:03:56.898
Can't we survive
on the dole?

01:03:56.900 --> 01:03:58.567
-Shame on you!
-Oh, what should I do?

01:03:58.569 --> 01:04:00.268
Do you have any plans?

01:04:01.505 --> 01:04:03.572
My angel,
please don't leave me.

01:04:05.475 --> 01:04:06.975
I love you very much.

01:04:08.245 --> 01:04:09.411
[SIGHS IN EXASPERATION]

01:04:21.925 --> 01:04:23.658
Here's an idea.

01:04:23.660 --> 01:04:25.894
Borrowed from
a Korean movie I'd seen.

01:04:27.297 --> 01:04:30.565
It's about an unemployed guy
with little savings,

01:04:30.567 --> 01:04:33.568
and he has a wife
and a young son to support.

01:04:33.570 --> 01:04:36.638
So he tricks
his insurance company
and makes claims.

01:04:38.675 --> 01:04:40.876
How is that possible?

01:04:40.878 --> 01:04:43.545
Insurance is paid
for death and injury.

01:04:45.482 --> 01:04:46.915
So, kill.

01:04:47.885 --> 01:04:49.384
Or someone gets hurt.

01:04:50.354 --> 01:04:51.453
Not quite.

01:04:52.456 --> 01:04:53.989
Don't worry, let it be.

01:04:55.392 --> 01:04:56.658
Stories have a purpose.

01:04:57.327 --> 01:04:58.426
Not always.

01:04:59.129 --> 01:05:00.462
Tell me anyway.

01:05:03.467 --> 01:05:05.500
The guy cuts off
one of his limbs

01:05:05.502 --> 01:05:07.669
and lodges a claim
to the insurance company.

01:05:09.406 --> 01:05:10.939
And then, he does it again.

01:05:12.309 --> 01:05:13.541
Why would he do that?

01:05:14.411 --> 01:05:15.977
All for his loved ones.

01:05:24.922 --> 01:05:26.721
[ARIF HUMMING TUNE]

01:05:37.401 --> 01:05:39.267
[COUGHS] Sorry.

01:05:47.678 --> 01:05:50.378
My father and I watched
a lot of movies on TV.

01:05:51.415 --> 01:05:53.615
Both of us
loved Korean movies.

01:05:55.953 --> 01:05:58.954
How come you don't
even have a TV?

01:05:58.956 --> 01:06:02.457
Don't you sit in pubs
and watch rugby
like other Aussies?

01:06:02.459 --> 01:06:03.591
No.

01:06:03.593 --> 01:06:06.428
Pubs and parties
are frivolous.

01:06:06.430 --> 01:06:07.662
-And rugby?
-[SNICKERS]

01:06:07.664 --> 01:06:09.230
It's too violent.

01:06:11.969 --> 01:06:13.535
Some TV shows are interesting.

01:06:14.571 --> 01:06:17.272
It's a complete
waste of time.

01:06:17.274 --> 01:06:19.774
No wonder
it's called the idiot box.

01:06:19.776 --> 01:06:24.145
Moreover, what upsets me more,

01:06:24.147 --> 01:06:27.415
the world is just
so full of bad news.

01:06:28.352 --> 01:06:29.417
Oh.

01:06:30.354 --> 01:06:32.287
What bothers you?

01:06:32.289 --> 01:06:35.223
There's just so much hatred
out there, for no reason.

01:06:35.225 --> 01:06:37.225
War, terrorism.

01:06:38.595 --> 01:06:39.728
Hmm.

01:06:42.733 --> 01:06:44.766
[SNICKERS]
The world's a mess.

01:06:46.436 --> 01:06:48.370
And it's so complex.

01:06:50.207 --> 01:06:54.642
My father reminisces
about his childhood
growing up in Ireland.

01:06:54.644 --> 01:06:58.313
Just makes me think
we've lost that simple world,
you know?

01:07:06.523 --> 01:07:08.556
I wonder what happened
with the missing girl.

01:07:09.292 --> 01:07:10.725
Did the cops find out?

01:07:14.264 --> 01:07:15.597
Her name is familiar.

01:07:17.634 --> 01:07:19.034
Kathy, remember?

01:07:20.470 --> 01:07:22.537
How do you expect me
to know about her?

01:07:24.374 --> 01:07:26.274
The cops showed her photo.

01:07:26.276 --> 01:07:28.043
Can we please
stop this discussion?

01:07:30.313 --> 01:07:32.814
It's just that I seem
to know something.

01:07:33.683 --> 01:07:35.316
Just don't know what.

01:07:43.560 --> 01:07:44.659
Sorry.

01:07:45.729 --> 01:07:46.828
Okay?

01:07:48.598 --> 01:07:51.366
Well, I'm going to
take a quick shower.

01:07:53.370 --> 01:07:54.636
Won't you join me?

01:08:14.191 --> 01:08:18.792
NOEL: Back home in Ireland,
children took care
of their parents.

01:08:18.795 --> 01:08:23.331
Here, I have to
kick and scream
to get anything.

01:08:23.332 --> 01:08:24.732
LIAM: What do you want?

01:08:26.670 --> 01:08:30.505
NOEL: You can't even
provide me with what I want.

01:08:30.506 --> 01:08:33.441
You're as useless
as tits on a bull.

01:08:33.443 --> 01:08:35.276
What a shame.

01:08:36.746 --> 01:08:39.581
We've had this
conversation before.
No more!

01:08:45.788 --> 01:08:48.288
-Why not?
-Please.

01:08:49.326 --> 01:08:51.559
[SCOFFS] I know why not.

01:08:52.828 --> 01:08:54.529
Because you want it.

01:09:02.572 --> 01:09:03.770
Give him what he wants.

01:09:03.773 --> 01:09:05.807
Stay out of this.

01:09:05.809 --> 01:09:07.774
No matter what I do,
it's never enough.

01:09:09.479 --> 01:09:12.313
NOEL: I wish Conan was here.

01:09:12.314 --> 01:09:14.616
He would've done
everything for me.

01:09:19.756 --> 01:09:22.323
Why does he
ridicule you all the time?

01:09:24.493 --> 01:09:27.295
You are a disgrace as a son!

01:09:33.435 --> 01:09:35.336
After all I have one for you,

01:09:36.740 --> 01:09:39.174
this is what
you have to say?

01:09:39.176 --> 01:09:41.709
Yes! Yes, and yes!

01:09:42.645 --> 01:09:46.413
She is the source
of all evil.

01:09:46.416 --> 01:09:48.166
She's bewitched you!

01:09:48.167 --> 01:09:49.917
-Turned you
into a horrible son!
-[ZOYA SOBBING]

01:09:57.260 --> 01:09:58.526
[ZOYA SOBBING]

01:09:58.528 --> 01:10:00.428
NOEL: Get rid of your doll.

01:10:00.430 --> 01:10:01.829
Right now!

01:10:05.602 --> 01:10:07.602
You are evil.

01:10:08.772 --> 01:10:10.805
You are the devil.

01:10:15.378 --> 01:10:16.477
[DOOR OPENING]

01:10:16.479 --> 01:10:17.745
[BOTTLE CLATTERING]

01:10:17.747 --> 01:10:19.480
[NOEL GRUNTING]

01:10:22.752 --> 01:10:25.720
NOEL: Help! Help me!

01:10:25.722 --> 01:10:27.255
[STRUGGLING] Liam!

01:10:29.726 --> 01:10:34.829
LIAM: If you confess your sins,
He is faithful and just,

01:10:34.831 --> 01:10:39.567
and will forgive your sins
and purify you
from all unrighteousness.

01:10:40.036 --> 01:10:42.237
So, confess.

01:10:42.239 --> 01:10:43.771
[NOEL CHOKING]

01:10:44.641 --> 01:10:46.407
[GRUNTING]

01:10:46.409 --> 01:10:47.675
NOEL: Serves you right.

01:10:48.612 --> 01:10:50.044
[NOEL GRUNTING]

01:10:58.288 --> 01:10:59.721
NOEL: Help me!

01:11:01.791 --> 01:11:02.857
Help!

01:11:04.761 --> 01:11:10.331
-LIAM: I am going to kill you.
-[CHOKING]

01:11:26.383 --> 01:11:28.349
[ZOYA WHIMPERING]

01:11:47.737 --> 01:11:49.671
[GROANING]

01:11:53.777 --> 01:11:54.909
Angel!

01:11:56.680 --> 01:11:58.413
Where are you?

01:12:00.317 --> 01:12:01.683
I need your help.

01:12:11.594 --> 01:12:12.660
[GRUNTS]

01:12:14.064 --> 01:12:16.664
Angel, why are you hiding?

01:12:19.703 --> 01:12:21.602
[GRUNTING]

01:12:29.446 --> 01:12:30.511
[GROANS]

01:12:35.785 --> 01:12:38.086
You don't have to be afraid.

01:12:41.691 --> 01:12:43.891
We can now live
without fear.

01:12:45.662 --> 01:12:47.595
-[DOOR LOCKS]
-No!

01:12:52.569 --> 01:12:53.768
[SOBBING]

01:13:12.789 --> 01:13:13.955
[DOOR RATTLING]

01:13:37.680 --> 01:13:39.213
Since I was a child...

01:13:40.650 --> 01:13:42.550
Father kept me in a dark room.

01:13:44.220 --> 01:13:45.953
I've been afraid of the dark
ever since.

01:14:01.704 --> 01:14:03.504
I brought you light.

01:14:04.073 --> 01:14:05.573
I brought you food.

01:14:07.444 --> 01:14:10.178
I brought you
out of the dungeon.
Remember?

01:14:10.180 --> 01:14:13.881
ZOYA: I really thought
you were my knight
in shining armor.

01:14:16.252 --> 01:14:18.152
You tricked
and deceived me.

01:14:20.690 --> 01:14:23.257
It wasn't me, it was Conan.

01:14:23.860 --> 01:14:26.160
My angel, please.

01:14:27.697 --> 01:14:29.197
Please help me.

01:14:31.668 --> 01:14:33.267
Please don't do this to me.

01:14:37.240 --> 01:14:38.706
You love me.

01:14:40.477 --> 01:14:41.542
And I love you.

01:14:42.145 --> 01:14:43.644
[LIAM SOBBING]

01:14:48.218 --> 01:14:49.550
[LIAM SNIFFLING]

01:14:55.525 --> 01:14:58.526
"You have heard
that it was said,

01:14:58.528 --> 01:15:03.130
"'Love your neighbor
and hate your enemy.'"

01:15:13.209 --> 01:15:14.876
Do you know
the meaning of my name?

01:15:16.880 --> 01:15:19.614
Liam. Comes from William.

01:15:21.885 --> 01:15:23.718
It means "strong protector."

01:15:23.720 --> 01:15:25.186
[ZOYA LAUGHING]

01:15:33.329 --> 01:15:36.664
-I protected you
from all evil.
-[CONTINUES LAUGHING]

01:15:46.309 --> 01:15:50.278
You had no chance of escape
if I hadn't helped you.

01:15:53.583 --> 01:15:55.583
Did you tell me
a story about a frog?

01:15:58.922 --> 01:16:01.689
I'll tell you
another story of a frog.

01:16:04.861 --> 01:16:08.296
One day a frog fell
into a pail

01:16:08.298 --> 01:16:11.933
that was half-filled
with fresh milk.

01:16:13.336 --> 01:16:15.736
The sides of the pail
were high,

01:16:15.738 --> 01:16:19.707
and the level of the milk
was too low for the frog
to jump out.

01:16:21.177 --> 01:16:23.644
He kicked and screamed.

01:16:25.281 --> 01:16:28.249
There was no one
to help the frog escape.

01:16:28.251 --> 01:16:32.253
And he grew tired.

01:16:32.255 --> 01:16:34.822
But every time
he quit kicking,

01:16:34.824 --> 01:16:37.959
he sank into the milk
and started to drown.

01:16:40.063 --> 01:16:41.829
So he kept kicking.

01:16:45.602 --> 01:16:46.968
Do you know what happened?

01:16:49.706 --> 01:16:51.272
Something strange happened.

01:16:53.276 --> 01:16:55.910
The milk began to
turn thicker around him.

01:16:57.380 --> 01:17:00.982
At first, this made kicking
even harder.

01:17:02.852 --> 01:17:04.685
But the frog didn't give up.

01:17:05.788 --> 01:17:10.358
Finally, the milk
had turned thick enough

01:17:10.360 --> 01:17:14.328
for the frog
to stand on top of it
instead of sinking in.

01:17:15.932 --> 01:17:18.366
The milk had been
turned into butter

01:17:18.368 --> 01:17:22.837
through all the kicking
and turning and churning
of the frog.

01:17:22.839 --> 01:17:24.705
The frog was able
to climb out to safety...

01:17:28.277 --> 01:17:29.944
and return to his family.

01:17:31.914 --> 01:17:34.649
I have loved you
every moment.

01:17:35.752 --> 01:17:36.817
Believe me.

01:17:37.887 --> 01:17:39.820
Please. Save me again.

01:17:41.157 --> 01:17:42.390
You saved me once.

01:17:44.160 --> 01:17:45.726
Please save me again.

01:17:48.264 --> 01:17:49.330
[OBJECT CLATTERING]

01:17:52.402 --> 01:17:54.268
Angel, no.

01:17:55.271 --> 01:17:56.837
No!

01:17:56.839 --> 01:17:58.372
[DOOR LOCKING]

01:18:00.910 --> 01:18:02.309
[SOBBING]

01:18:36.512 --> 01:18:38.813
LIAM: <i> "You have heard</i>
<i> that it was said,</i>

01:18:38.815 --> 01:18:41.749
<i> '"Love your neighbor</i>
<i> and hate your enemy.'"</i>

01:18:41.751 --> 01:18:44.518
<i> "But I tell you,</i>
<i> love your enemies</i>

01:18:44.520 --> 01:18:47.722
<i> "and pray for those</i>
<i> who persecute you,</i>

01:18:47.724 --> 01:18:50.925
<i> "that you may be children</i>
<i> of your Father in heaven.</i>

01:18:50.927 --> 01:18:52.193
[GATE CREAKING]

01:18:52.195 --> 01:18:58.766
<i> "He causes the sun to rise</i>
<i> on the evil and the good,</i>

01:18:58.768 --> 01:19:03.471
<i> "and sends rain</i>
<i> on the righteous</i>
<i> and unrighteous."</i>

01:19:30.500 --> 01:19:31.999
-[BIRDS CHIRPING]
-[SHEARS SNIPPING]

01:19:49.852 --> 01:19:50.918
[IN HINDI]

01:19:58.461 --> 01:20:00.194
Papa.

01:20:00.196 --> 01:20:02.463
-[IN ENGLISH] I'm sorry, Papa.
-I missed you so much.

01:20:02.465 --> 01:20:05.299
-I'm sorry, Papa.
-I missed you so much.

01:20:05.301 --> 01:20:07.201
I'm sorry, Papa.

01:20:12.375 --> 01:20:14.441
[INDISTINCT TALKING ON TV]

01:20:15.278 --> 01:20:16.477
[MUTES TV]

01:20:21.450 --> 01:20:23.217
[ARIF SPEAKING HINDI]

01:20:29.859 --> 01:20:31.358
[IN ENGLISH] I'm sorry, Papa.

01:20:32.328 --> 01:20:33.527
[IN HINDI]

01:20:37.567 --> 01:20:38.933
[ZOYA SNICKERS]

01:20:42.371 --> 01:20:43.604
[ZOYA CHUCKLING]

01:20:52.915 --> 01:20:55.249
FEMALE REPORTER: [ON TV]
<i> A missing girl, Kathy Young,</i>
<i> has been found</i>

01:20:55.251 --> 01:20:57.418
<i> wandering near her home</i>
<i> in Bathurst.</i>

01:20:57.420 --> 01:20:59.587
<i> She had been missing for</i>
<i> almost three-and-half years,</i>

01:20:59.589 --> 01:21:02.857
<i> and appeared disoriented</i>
<i> and severely malnourished.</i>

01:21:02.859 --> 01:21:05.960
<i> Not much is known</i>
<i> about her disappearance</i>
<i> at this stage.</i>

01:21:22.411 --> 01:21:24.345
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

01:21:34.257 --> 01:21:35.456
[BREATH TREMBLING]

01:21:36.292 --> 01:21:37.391
Police?

01:21:38.294 --> 01:21:40.961
Please. Please help me.

01:21:42.131 --> 01:21:45.299
My angel, she's gone crazy.

01:21:46.702 --> 01:21:48.903
She has sworn to kill me.

01:21:48.905 --> 01:21:50.371
[SNIFFLES]

01:21:50.373 --> 01:21:52.907
God, I loved her.

01:21:52.909 --> 01:21:54.541
I loved her.

01:21:57.380 --> 01:21:58.646
I loved her.

01:21:59.615 --> 01:22:01.015
I loved her.

01:22:01.717 --> 01:22:04.218
[SOBBING]

01:22:10.192 --> 01:22:11.358
[SNIFFLES]

01:22:13.262 --> 01:22:15.462
[ARIF SPEAKING HINDI]

01:22:26.142 --> 01:22:27.408
[ARIF CHUCKLES]
